---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import { authors } from '../../data/authors';
import type { Author } from '../../types/blog';

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  const posts = [
    {
      slug: "what-drives-painting-prices",
      title: "What Drives the Price of a Painting? An Insider's Guide",
      description: "Explore the key factors that influence art valuations and market prices. From artist reputation to provenance, understand what makes certain artworks more valuable than others.",
      publishDate: "March 15, 2024",
      readingTime: "7 min read",
      category: "MARKET INSIGHTS",
      author: "sarah-johnson",
      image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1577083288073-40892c0860a4?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop",
      content: `
        <p class="lead">The art market is often perceived as mysterious and unpredictable, but there are several key factors that consistently influence the value of paintings. Understanding these drivers is crucial for both collectors and investors looking to make informed decisions in the art market.</p>

        <h2>1. Artist Reputation and Market Position</h2>
        <p>An artist's reputation is perhaps the most significant factor in determining a painting's value. This includes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Historical significance and influence on other artists</li>
          <li>Representation by prestigious galleries</li>
          <li>Presence in major museum collections</li>
          <li>Exhibition history and critical reception</li>
          <li>Market performance history</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Provenance and Authentication</h2>
        <p>The artwork's history of ownership and verification of authenticity are crucial value drivers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Documentation of previous owners</li>
          <li>Exhibition history</li>
          <li>Certificates of authenticity</li>
          <li>Inclusion in the artist's catalogue raisonné</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Condition and Conservation</h2>
        <p>The physical condition of a painting significantly impacts its value:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Original condition vs. restoration history</li>
          <li>Quality of conservation work</li>
          <li>Storage and display history</li>
          <li>Environmental exposure</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Market Timing and Economic Factors</h2>
        <p>External market conditions play a crucial role in pricing:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Overall art market conditions</li>
          <li>Economic climate</li>
          <li>Collector demand for specific periods or styles</li>
          <li>Availability of similar works</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Technical and Aesthetic Qualities</h2>
        <p>The intrinsic qualities of the artwork itself matter significantly:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Size and scale</li>
          <li>Medium and materials</li>
          <li>Technical execution</li>
          <li>Subject matter and composition</li>
          <li>Period in artist's career</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Understanding Value Appreciation</h2>
        <p>Art values typically appreciate through a combination of these factors strengthening over time. For example, an artist's reputation may grow through increased institutional recognition, while scarcity increases as works enter permanent collections.</p>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>While art valuation involves many variables, understanding these key drivers helps investors make more informed decisions. Regular monitoring of these factors can provide insights into potential value changes and investment opportunities in the art market.</p>
      `
    },
    {
      slug: "global-events-art-market",
      title: "The Impact of Global Events on Art Markets",
      description: "An in-depth analysis of how global events shape art market dynamics and create new opportunities for investors.",
      publishDate: "March 14, 2024",
      readingTime: "6 min read",
      category: "MARKET INSIGHTS",
      author: "michael-chen",
      image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1541367777708-7905fe3296c0?q=80&w=2069&auto=format&fit=crop",
      content: `
        <p class="lead">Global events have always played a significant role in shaping art market dynamics. From economic shifts to cultural movements, understanding these impacts is crucial for art investors.</p>

        <h2>Economic Impact</h2>
        <p>Major economic events can significantly affect art market behavior:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Market volatility during economic uncertainty</li>
          <li>Currency fluctuations affecting international sales</li>
          <li>Changes in collector behavior during recessions</li>
          <li>Impact on gallery and auction house operations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cultural Shifts</h2>
        <p>Cultural changes can create new opportunities and challenges:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Rising interest in diverse artists and perspectives</li>
          <li>Changing collector demographics</li>
          <li>Evolution of artistic mediums and themes</li>
          <li>Impact of social movements on art values</li>
        </ul>
      `
    }
  ];

  return posts.map(post => ({
    params: { slug: post.slug },
    props: { post, author: authors[post.author] }
  }));
}

const { post, author } = Astro.props;
---

<BlogLayout
  title={post.title}
  description={post.description}
  publishDate={post.publishDate}
  readingTime={post.readingTime}
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="mb-16">
      <img 
        src={post.image} 
        alt={post.title}
        class="w-full aspect-[2/1] object-cover rounded-2xl"
      />
    </div>

    <header class="mb-16">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <span class="text-sm font-medium text-purple">{post.category}</span>
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-serif leading-tight text-gray-900">{post.title}</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 font-light leading-relaxed">{post.description}</p>
        
        <!-- Author Byline -->
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-4 pt-8">
          <img 
            src={author.image} 
            alt={author.name}
            class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full object-cover"
          />
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
              <h3 class="text-base font-medium text-gray-900">{author.name}</h3>
              <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
                {author.twitter && (
                  <a 
                    href={`https://twitter.com/${author.twitter}`}
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="text-gray-400 hover:text-purple transition-colors"
                  >
                    <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                      <path d="M18.244 2.25h3.308l-7.227 8.26 8.502 11.24H16.17l-5.214-6.817L4.99 21.75H1.68l7.73-8.835L1.254 2.25H8.08l4.713 6.231zm-1.161 17.52h1.833L7.084 4.126H5.117z"/>
                    </svg>
                  </a>
                )}
                {author.linkedin && (
                  <a 
                    href={`https://linkedin.com/${author.linkedin}`}
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="text-gray-400 hover:text-purple transition-colors"
                  >
                    <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                      <path d="M20.5 2h-17A1.5 1.5 0 002 3.5v17A1.5 1.5 0 003.5 22h17a1.5 1.5 0 001.5-1.5v-17A1.5 1.5 0 0020.5 2zM8 19H5v-9h3zM6.5 8.25A1.75 1.75 0 118.3 6.5a1.78 1.78 0 01-1.8 1.75zM19 19h-3v-4.74c0-1.42-.6-1.93-1.38-1.93A1.74 1.74 0 0013 14.19a.66.66 0 000 .14V19h-3v-9h2.9v1.3a3.11 3.11 0 012.7-1.4c1.55 0 3.36.86 3.36 3.66z"></path>
                    </svg>
                  </a>
                )}
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">
              <span>{author.title}</span>
              <span class="mx-2">•</span>
              <time>{post.publishDate}</time>
              <span class="mx-2">•</span>
              <span>{post.readingTime}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-gray mx-auto">
      <style is:inline>
        .prose .lead {
          font-size: 1.375rem;
          line-height: 1.7;
          margin-top: 0;
          margin-bottom: 2rem;
          color: #4B5563;
          font-weight: 300;
        }
        .prose h2 {
          font-family: var(--font-serif);
          font-weight: normal;
          font-size: 2rem;
          margin-top: 3rem;
          margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
          color: #111827;
        }
        .prose p {
          margin-top: 1.5rem;
          margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
          line-height: 1.75;
          color: #374151;
        }
        .prose ul {
          margin-top: 1.5rem;
          margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
          list-style-type: disc;
          padding-left: 1.625rem;
        }
        .prose li {
          margin-top: 0.75rem;
          margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
          padding-left: 0.375rem;
          color: #374151;
        }
      </style>
      <div set:html={post.content} />
    </div>

    <!-- Author Bio -->
    <footer class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
      <div class="flex items-start space-x-6">
        <img 
          src={author.image} 
          alt={author.name}
          class="w-20 h-20 rounded-full object-cover"
        />
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">About {author.name}</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">{author.bio}</p>
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
            {author.twitter && (
              <a 
                href={`https://twitter.com/${author.twitter}`}
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-gray-400 hover:text-purple transition-colors"
              >
                Follow on Twitter
              </a>
            )}
            {author.linkedin && (
              <a 
                href={`https://linkedin.com/${author.linkedin}`}
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-gray-400 hover:text-purple transition-colors"
              >
                Connect on LinkedIn
              </a>
            )}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </article>
</BlogLayout>